Vice President Biden met with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan to discuss the U.S.-Japan alliance and cooperation on regional and global issues. They emphasized the importance of the alliance for regional peace and stability and expressed their goal of enhancing the alliance and expanding security cooperation. They also discussed Japan's participation in the Trans-Pacific Partnership (TPP) and the need to deepen trade and investment ties. On regional security, they reaffirmed the U.S. position on the East China Sea and stressed the importance of reducing tensions. They also agreed on the need for close coordination in addressing North Korea's provocations and its denuclearization obligations.